</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5FA71FB029BE4" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" box="[174,1233,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5FA71FB029BE4" box="[174,1233,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">— Eyes holoptic. ...................................................................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30932E42744AFFE4C4A5FA6CFB02982E" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5FA6CFB029809" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" box="[174,1233,1535,1557]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5FA6CFB029809" box="[174,1233,1535,1557]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
2 Wing base bright yellow; body dark olive green. ............ 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D64744AFFE4C71DFA6CFB029809" authority="(Stackelberg, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Stackelberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[790,1233,1535,1557]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="jaroslavensis">
<emphasis id="B913EAF5744AFFE4C71DFA6CFBC09808" box="[790,1043,1535,1556]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Melanogaster jaroslavensis</emphasis>
(Stackelberg, 1922)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F98FFB02982E" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" box="[174,1233,1564,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F98FFB02982E" box="[174,1233,1564,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">— Wing base darkened, blackish or brownish; body black. .............................................................................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30932E42744AFFE4C4A5F9AAFB0398B9" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F9AAFB029870" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F9AAFB029870" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
3 Tergite 8 with short pile (as long as diameter of hind ocellus); surstylus less than twice as long as wide. .................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D64744AFFE4C767F9C5FB029870" authority="(Macquart, 1829)" authorityName="Stackelberg" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[876,1233,1622,1644]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nuda">
<emphasis id="B913EAF5744AFFE4C767F9C5FBF79877" box="[876,1060,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Melanogaster nuda</emphasis>
(Macquart, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F9E1FB0398B9" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F9E1FB0398B9" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">— Tergite 8 with long pile (noticeably longer than diameter of hind ocellus); surstylus 2–3 times longer than wide..............................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30932E42744AFFE4C4A5F93FFB0298C3" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F93FFB0298DE" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" box="[174,1233,1708,1730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F93FFB0298DE" box="[174,1233,1708,1730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">4 Scutum with pale and black pile, pale pile often more abundant. ............................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F95AFB0298C3" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" box="[174,1233,1737,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F95AFB0298C3" box="[174,1233,1737,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">— Scutum with black pile. ...................................................................................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30932E42744AFFE7C4A5F975FB1B9EE2" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph id="8BD836E7744AFFE4C4A5F975FB039929" blockId="5.[174,1233,1478,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead id="309695D2744AFFE4C4A5F975FB039929" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
5 Mesonotum covered with long and short pale and black pile mixed; face broad: ratio of the maximum head width to the face width at the level right under the antennal base 1.91–2.08; surstylus with apex not curved. ............................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D64744AFFE4C7F2F8B3FB039929" authority="Loew, 1843" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1843" box="[1017,1232,1823,1845]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis id="B913EAF5744AFFE4C7F2F8B3FB8D9928" box="[1017,1118,1823,1845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">M. hirtella</emphasis>
Loew, 1843
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E77449FFE7C4ADFF3CFB1B9EE2" blockId="6.[166,1225,175,456]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="309695D27449FFE7C4ADFF3CFB1B9EE2" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
— Mesonotum covered with short pale (yellowish) pile almost equally short; face narrow: ratio of the maximum head width to the face width at the level right under the antennal base 2.27–2.37; surstylus with curved apex. ....................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647449FFE7C774FF7AFB1B9EE2" authority="Vujic &amp; Stuke, 1998" authorityName="Vujic &amp; Stuke" authorityYear="1998" box="[895,1224,232,254]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="curvistylus">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57449FFE7C774FF7AFBD79EE2" box="[895,1028,233,254]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">M. curvistylus</emphasis>
Vujić &amp; Stuke, 1998
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30932E427449FFE7C4ADFE96FB1A9FD4" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<paragraph id="8BD836E77449FFE7C4ADFE96FB1A9F6E" blockId="6.[166,1225,175,456]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="309695D27449FFE7C4ADFE96FB1A9F6E" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
6 Facial tubercle distinctly elongated and pointed (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627449FFE7C6D9FE96FCC19F07" box="[722,786,261,283]" captionStart="Figs 13–16" captionStartId="4.[167,206,1167,1189]" captionTargetBox="[170,1228,174,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-306@4.[170,1229,174,1141]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 13–16. Melanogaster parumplicata (figs 13, 14) and M. aerosa (figs 15, 16): 13, 15 — head, male, lateral view (arrow shows facial tubercle); 14, 16 — head, female, lateral view (arrow shows a transition from upper to lower part of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377549" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377549/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">fig. 15</figureCitation>
); face narrower: ratio of the maximum head width to the face width at the level just below the antennal base 2.2 (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627449FFE7C787FEB1FC189F24" box="[908,971,290,312]" captionStart="Figs 17–20" captionStartId="5.[174,213,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-270@5.[174,1233,174,1082]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17–20. Melanogaster parumplicata (figs 17, 18) and M. aerosa (figs 19, 20): 17, 19 — head, male, frontal view; 18, 20 — head, female, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377551/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">fig. 19</figureCitation>
); scutum, especially notopleuron and lateral side of scutum posterior to transverse suture often with a slight bronze or copper tint. ................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647449FFE7C7E3FECFFB1A9F6E" authority="(Loew, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1000,1225,348,370]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aerosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57449FFE7C7E3FECFFB969F6D" box="[1000,1093,348,369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">M. aerosa</emphasis>
(Loew, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E77449FFE7C4ADFEEBFB1A9FD4" blockId="6.[166,1225,175,456]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<keyLead id="309695D27449FFE7C4ADFEEBFB1A9FD4" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
— Facial tubercle weakly developed and flattened (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627449FFE7C6B2FEEBFD259F92" box="[697,758,376,398]" captionStart="Figs 13–16" captionStartId="4.[167,206,1167,1189]" captionTargetBox="[170,1228,174,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-306@4.[170,1229,174,1141]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 13–16. Melanogaster parumplicata (figs 13, 14) and M. aerosa (figs 15, 16): 13, 15 — head, male, lateral view (arrow shows facial tubercle); 14, 16 — head, female, lateral view (arrow shows a transition from upper to lower part of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377549" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377549/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">fig. 13</figureCitation>
); face broader: ratio of the maximum head width to the face width at the level just below the antennal base 1.95–2.0 (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627449FFE7C79FFE06FC079FB7" box="[916,980,405,427]" captionStart="Figs 17–20" captionStartId="5.[174,213,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-270@5.[174,1233,174,1082]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17–20. Melanogaster parumplicata (figs 17, 18) and M. aerosa (figs 19, 20): 17, 19 — head, male, frontal view; 18, 20 — head, female, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377551/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">fig. 17</figureCitation>
); scutum mostly shining black. ................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647449FFE7C7AEFE20FB1A9FD4" authority="(Loew, 1840)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[933,1225,434,456]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parumplicata">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57449FFE7C7AEFE20FB959FDB" box="[933,1094,434,456]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">M. parumplicata</emphasis>
(Loew, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
